abstract: Representative Zoe Lofgren seemed to relish comparing Nixon’s direction to his administration during Watergate with what White House lawyers said in an October letter about the current inquiry.
snippet: Representative Zoe Lofgren seemed to relish comparing Nixon’s direction to his administration during Watergate with what White House lawyers said in an October letter about the current inquiry.
lead_paragraph: Democrats don’t usually hold up President Richard M. Nixon as a paragon of transparency. Yet in making their case on Friday that President Trump was unprecedented in his obstruction of Congress, they did just that.
headline_main: In describing Trump’s actions, Democrats hold up Nixon as transparent.

abstract: He disputed the assertion from House managers that Hunter Biden’s involvement in Burisma, a Ukrainian energy company, had been investigated.
snippet: He disputed the assertion from House managers that Hunter Biden’s involvement in Burisma, a Ukrainian energy company, had been investigated.
lead_paragraph: Senator Lindsey Graham told reporters this morning that he wants someone “like Mueller” to investigate Joe and Hunter Biden and their activity in Ukraine years ago, a reference to Robert S. Mueller III, the former special counsel who examined Russian interference in the 2016 election.

lead_paragraph: The administration, at the direction of the White House, stonewalled 71 requests for documents by House investigators. abstract: In the run-up to the U.S. 2020 presidential election, many Democratic White House contenders have argued in favor of either breaking up or tightening regulation of companies such as Facebook Inc, Alphabet Inc's Google and Amazon.com Inc.

abstract: The top lawyer for the House of Representatives notified the Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia of the inconsistent legal positions, and urged swift rulings for the House.
snippet: The top lawyer for the House of Representatives notified the Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia of the inconsistent legal positions, and urged swift rulings for the House.
lead_paragraph: Last year, as the Trump administration battled House Democrats in court over information for oversight investigations, the Justice Department said that such matters were a “purely political dispute” and that the House lacked standing to ask the judicial branch to enforce its subpoenas.
headline_main: White House team has contradicted Justice Dept., House lawyer says.

abstract: Top officials from the U.S. State Department will conduct a classified briefing next week on Iran policy for members of the Senate Foreign Relations Committee, the committee said on Friday, amid a push for legislation to restrict President Donald Trump's ability to wage war on Iran.
snippet: Top officials from the U.S. State Department will conduct a classified briefing next week on Iran policy for members of the Senate Foreign Relations Committee, the committee said on Friday, amid a push for legislation to restrict President Donald ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Top officials from the U.S. State Department will conduct a classified briefing next week on Iran policy for members of the Senate Foreign Relations Committee, the committee said on Friday, amid a push for legislation to restrict President Donald Trump's ability to wage war on Iran.
headline_main: Trump Administration Officials to Brief Senators on Iran Next Week

abstract: The Trump administration said on Friday that California cannot require health insurers to cover abortions and threatened to cut some federal healthcare funds unless it pulls that requirement.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — The Trump administration said on Friday that California cannot require health insurers to cover abortions and threatened to cut some federal healthcare funds unless it pulls that requirement.

abstract: Donald Trump became the first U.S. president to attend the annual March for Life in Washington on Friday, unleashing a fierce attack on his Democratic rivals during a rally in an election-year show of support for opponents of abortion rights.
snippet: Donald Trump became the first U.S. president to attend the annual March for Life in Washington on Friday, unleashing a fierce attack on his Democratic rivals during a rally in an election-year show of support for opponents of abortion rights.

headline_main: At Anti-Abortion Rally, Trump Assails Democrats, Draws Applause

abstract: The Senate had asked the president’s lawyers to limit their presentation on Saturday to no more than three hours, Jay Sekulow said.
snippet: The Senate had asked the president’s lawyers to limit their presentation on Saturday to no more than three hours, Jay Sekulow said.
lead_paragraph: Jay Sekulow, a member of President Trump’s legal team, said during a break in the impeachment trial on Friday that the defense would present a brief overview of its case on Saturday, comparing it to a movie trailer.
headline_main: Sekulow compares Saturday defense to ‘a coming attraction.’
